+# LX Coordinate Remap DataOp Sketch
+
+This is the minimal backend interface needed by Torch-Spyre's
+`lx_coordinate_remap_v0` artifact metadata. It is intentionally not an STCDP
+extension: STCDP overlaps source and destination pieces, while SwiGLU
+matmul-to-pointwise handoff needs an explicit logical source rectangle to
+logical destination rectangle copy between different per-core LX layouts.
+
+## DataOp
+
+Add a data-op named `LXCoordinateRemapOp` accepted in a mixed SuperDSC before a
+consumer DL row.
+
+```json
+{
+  "op": {"name": "LXCoordinateRemapOp"},
+  "schemaVersion": 0,
+  "sourceName": "buf0",
+  "producer": "0_batchmatmul",
+  "consumer": "1_neg",
+  "dependencyOrder": [
+    {"order": 0, "kind": "producer_lx_write_before_remap"},
+    {"order": 1, "kind": "coordinate_remap"},
+    {"order": 2, "kind": "consumer_lx_read_after_remap"}
+  ],
+  "movements": [
+    {
+      "moveIndex": 0,
+      "bytes": 2048,
+      "source": {
+        "core": 4,
+        "logicalSlice": {
+          "starts": {"d0_": 1, "d1_": 0, "d2_": 0},
+          "sizes": {"d0_": 1, "d1_": 16, "d2_": 64}
+        },
+        "lxAddress": 0,
+        "byteRange": {"start": 0, "end": 2048}
+      },
+      "destination": {
+        "core": 0,
+        "logicalSlice": {
+          "starts": {"d0_": 1, "d1_": 0, "d2_": 0},
+          "sizes": {"d0_": 1, "d1_": 16, "d2_": 64}
+        },
+        "lxAddress": 1048578,
+        "byteRange": {"start": 1048578, "end": 1050626}
+      }
+    }
+  ]
+}
+```
+
+Torch-Spyre can also emit the flatter diagnostic form currently recorded in
+`onchip_move_plans.json`:
+
+```json
+{
+  "primitive": "lx_coordinate_remap_v0",
+  "movements": [
+    {
+      "source_core": 4,
+      "source_slice": {"starts": {"d0_": 1}, "sizes": {"d0_": 1}},
+      "source_lx_address": 0,
+      "source_lx_byte_range": {"start": 0, "end": 2048},
+      "destination_core": 0,
+      "destination_slice": {"starts": {"d0_": 1}, "sizes": {"d0_": 1}},
+      "destination_lx_address": 1048578,
+      "destination_lx_byte_range": {"start": 1048578, "end": 1050626}
+    }
+  ]
+}
+```
+
+## Required Semantics
+
+1. Treat `core` as the logical core in the surrounding SuperDSC schedule; do
+   not infer movement from physical core adjacency.
+2. Copy exactly `bytes` from source LX byte range to destination LX byte range.
+3. Use `logicalSlice` only for legality, diagnostics, and future physicalizer
+   rewrites; byte ranges define the actual LX transfer.
+4. Preserve dependency order:
+   producer DL row writes source LX before remap;
+   remap completes before consumer DL row reads destination LX.
+5. Reject overlapping destination byte ranges for the same destination core
+   unless every overlapping logical slice and byte range is identical.
+6. Reject source or destination ranges outside the producer/consumer LX region
+   provided by Torch-Spyre.
+
+## Why Current Carriers Are Insufficient
+
+`STCDPOpLx` can move overlapping pieces, but it does not express the destination
+local byte placement needed when producer and consumer `PerCoreView`s disagree.
+The existing mixed STCDP carrier can compile diagnostic JSON but cannot encode a
+general row-strided remap such as `{mb:4,out:8} -> {mb:32}` without backend-side
+physicalizer probes. `InputFetchNeighbor` is also not a replacement because the
+current backend path assumes `i/j` coordinates and one neighbor input.
+
+A first backend patch can import this data-op as an opaque scheduled row and
+lower each movement to the existing ring/LX copy mechanism after validating the
+coverage and dependency metadata above.
